0 What kind of a documentary about a musician fails to include a single track by the artist himself ? ! Unlike " Ray " or countless other films about music artists , half the fun in the theater ( or on the couch ) is reliving the great songs themselves . Here , all the tracks are covers put on by uninteresting characters , and these renditions fail to capture Cohen 's slow , jazzy style . More often , the covers are badly sung folk versions . Yuck.<br /><br />The interviews are as much or more with other musicians and figures rather than with Cohen himself . Only rarely does the film feature Cohen reading his own work ( never singing)-- like letters , poems , etc . The movie really did n't capture much about the artist 's life story , either , or about his development through the years . A huge disappointment for a big Cohen fan .
