0 Marlon Brando had long since lost interest in acting when he made this film . His performance as " The Swede " is the worst of his career , and that is precisely what he intended it to be . He does n't overact . Instead , he simply acts in a bizarre fashion and pokes fun at his embarrassingly gargantuan girth . The scene where Brando climbs over the toilet stall is probably the worst , funniest moment in the history of cinema . As we witness him fall head - first into a toilet , it is hard to believe that we are watching the same actor who starred in A Streetcar Named Desire , On the Waterfront , and The Godfather.<br /><br />I guess the real question is why Marlon behaved like this in his later years . Was he sick of the movie business ? Did he just like making a complete and utter fool out of himself ? I guess we 'll never know . But this film serves as a fascinating study as to what bad acting is all about.<br /><br />On that note , watch fellow acting veteran Donald Sutherland as he struggles to deliver his lines , embarrassed at himself for agreeing to participate in this travesty .
